Required
The Local-FIPS-State must contain valid FIPS codes based on the
jurisdiction table downloaded from the IRG. This always refers to
the first two digits of your stateâ€™s FIPS code.
The CSENet application will convert the Local-FIPS-State and
Other-FIPS-State on incoming transactions to keep the appropriate
point of reference.
You must have communications enabled for the specific
Functional-Type-Code with the state with which you are
communicating. The exchange agreement must be established in
the CSENet application.

Required
The Local-FIPS-County must contain valid FIPS codes based on
the jurisdiction table downloaded from the IRG. This always
refers to the 3rd, 4th and 5th digits of the state with which you are
communicating.
The CSENet application will convert the Local-FIPS-County and
Other-FIPS-County on incoming transactions to keep the
appropriate point of reference.
The value of the Local-FIPS-Sub portion of the FIPS code will not\nbe edited.

Required
The Other-FIPS-State must contain valid FIPS codes based on the
jurisdiction table downloaded from the IRG. This always refers to
the first two digits of the state with which you are communicating.
The CSENet application will convert the Local-FIPS-State and
Other-FIPS-State on incoming transactions to keep the appropriate
point of reference.
You must have communications enabled for the specific
Functional-Type-Code with the state with which you are
communicating. The exchange agreement must be established in
the CSENet application.

Required
The Other-FIPS-County must contain valid FIPS codes based on
the jurisdiction table downloaded from the IRG. This always
refers to the 3rd, 4th and 5th digits of the state with which you are
communicating.
The CSENet application will convert the Local-FIPS-County and
Other-FIPS-County on incoming transactions to keep the
appropriate point of reference.
You must have communications enabled for the specific
Functional-Type-Code with the state with which you are
communicating. The exchange agreement must be established in
the CSENet application.
The value of the Local-FIPS-Sub portion of the FIPS code will not\nbe edited.
